13/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kai Eide, UN special envoy for the review of democratic standards implementation on Kosovo, met with Serbian President Boris Tadic on Tuesday (12 July). 
Tadic told him that Serbs are willing to enter Kosovo's institutions, but only if progress is made in the decentralisation process. 
He also reiterated his readiness to meet with Kosovo counterpart Ibrahim Rugova. 
Eide separately met with Serbia-Montenegro Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic, discussing the same issues.
In other news Tuesday, the UN tribunal in The Hague decided to combine the trials of several people indicted for war crimes in Kosovo. 
The merger would include defendants Nikola Sainovic, Milan Milutinovic, Dragoljub Ojdanic, Nebojsa Pavkovic, Vladimir Lazarevic, Vlastimir Djordjevic and Sreten Lukic. 
The court said all are charged with similar crimes against Kosovo Albanian civilians committed between January and June of 1999. 
The pooled trial would begin in December or January. 
(RTS, B92, Tanjug - 12/07/05)
